				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: will this work?<a name="9023"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 10 03 3:10 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>On a lighter note even FT1 has a huge impact on our mana regen, mostly because our mana pool is typically much smaller than other casters.  I don't swarm kite, unless I absolutely have to, so I don't use as much mana as most on these boards.  However, one of the things I tend to use a lot while doing CC is our charm song.  Keeping one mob charmed while mezzing the others is very helpful since he'll play guard for you until you get things mezzed.  After you've got things under control send your pet in to assist the rest of the group and just keep the others mezzed.
<br />

<br />
In a situation where we have four mobs the group picks one, I charm one and mez the other two.  Then my twist is group haste, target mob and mez, group haste, target other mob and mez.  Some times I will try to get a slow on the mob, but this can be quite difficult at times since I'm also trying to keep the mobs in certain positions and we typically have a shaman with us.  It gets really harry when I'm main slower and CC heh, but I have done it before.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
