				<td colspan="2"><span>I am not quite sure what you mean by this, but I think that you might be the sad result of a bit of too much powerleveling...
<br />

<br />
My bard is 63, and every single skill he has other than tradeskills is maxed, and will never ever go up again...
<br />

<br />
Now the items I have that have +% to parry and repostle and dodge definately do work, as they cause a noticable difference on my parses of damage taken...even tho all my skills are maxxed, and have been for quite a few levels.
<br />

<br />
+% mod items are not for making up for people being powerleveled, they are to increase the effectiveness of a character in a certain aspect, and have no regard to the cap of that character.  Any +% item will have an effect, raising a certain attribute by the % listed, but not past 255.
<br />

<br />
...parry, repostle and dodge all go up MUCH faster than defense...yet you never see any +% Defense items for a reason...all tanking classes already have 252-255 defense as is, and +% to parry, repostle and dodge have much more effect, as the highest caps on these skills for any class is around 225 or so, thus leaving room for a +% to them to have an effect, as you cant raise a skill thats at 255 any higher.</span></td>
